<section class="page paper">
  <h1>What 47 Means</h1>

  <p>
    The number 47 is used here as a symbol of balance between grounded creation
    and spiritual awareness. The 4 represents foundation, discipline, structure,
    and the heart center. The 7 represents higher understanding, wisdom,
    intuition, and crown awareness.
  </p>

  <p>
    Chakra traditions come from Hindu and Tantric Buddhist systems where chakras
    are understood as subtle centers of psychic or spiritual energy, not physical
    organs. Britannica describes chakras as energy centers used in meditation and
    spiritual practice. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}
  </p>

  <p>
    Symbolically, the 4th chakra is connected to the heart: compassion, emotional
    truth, empathy, and connection. The 7th chakra is connected to the crown:
    spiritual awareness, unity, and higher consciousness.
  </p>

  <p>
    For RAK47, 4 + 7 means: build from the heart, move with vision, and create
    something that can be felt beyond sound.
  </p>
